<p><b>Andrew Lorne Campbell</b> (known as A. Lorne Campbell), <a href="/wiki/Order_of_Canada" title="Order of Canada">O.C.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Forces_Decoration" title="Canadian Forces Decoration">C.D.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Bachelor_of_Laws#Canada" title="Bachelor of Laws">LL.B.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Doctor_of_law#Canada" title="Doctor of law">LL.D.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Doctor_of_Canon_Law" title="Doctor of Canon Law">D.C.L.</a>, <a href="/wiki/Queen%27s_Counsel" title="Queen's Counsel">Q.C.</a> (1920 - January 15, 2014) was a Canadian lawyer in <a href="/wiki/Winnipeg,_Manitoba" title="Winnipeg, Manitoba" class="mw-redirect">Winnipeg, Manitoba</a>. He was very active in his community and in the legal profession, serving as President of the <a href="/wiki/Law_Society_of_Manitoba" title="Law Society of Manitoba">Law Society of Manitoba</a> and as the national President of the <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Bar_Association" title="Canadian Bar Association">Canadian Bar Association</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-cba_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-cba-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
